Step 1: Add 4 Dataverse columns
Go to Tables → Import Cycle → + New column for each:

Reference Controls New — Whole number, default 0
Reference Controls Updated — Whole number, default 0
Business Processes New — Whole number, default 0
Business Processes Updated — Whole number, default 0

Save and Publish.
Step 2: Add 4 variables in the flow
At the top of the flow where all Initialize variable actions are, add:

Initialize variable — Name: varRCNew, Type: Integer, Value: 0
Initialize variable — Name: varRCUpdated, Type: Integer, Value: 0
Initialize variable — Name: varBPNew, Type: Integer, Value: 0
Initialize variable — Name: varBPUpdated, Type: Integer, Value: 0

Step 3: Update RC loop
Delete Increment varRCCount (currently after the RC Exists condition).
Inside RC Exists → If No, after Create RC, add:

Increment variable — Name: varRCNew, Value: 1

Inside RC Exists → If Yes, after Update RC, add:

Increment variable — Name: varRCUpdated, Value: 1

Step 4: Update BP loop
Delete Increment varBPCount (currently after the BP Exists condition).
Inside BP Exists → If No, after Create BP, add:

Increment variable — Name: varBPNew, Value: 1

Inside BP Exists → If Yes, after Update BP, add:

Increment variable — Name: varBPUpdated, Value: 1

Step 5: Update Import Cycle Counts action
Remove the old varRCCount and varBPCount mappings. Add:

Reference Controls New → fx: variables('varRCNew')
Reference Controls Updated → fx: variables('varRCUpdated')
Business Processes New → fx: variables('varBPNew')
Business Processes Updated → fx: variables('varBPUpdated')

Step 6: Delete old variables
Delete the varRCCount and varBPCount Initialize variable actions at the top (we no longer use them).
